{"account":{"apiProvider":"firstParty","email":"kocienda@mac.com","organization":"kocienda@mac.com's Organization","subscriptionType":"Claude Max"},"agents":[],"available_output_styles":["default","Proactive","Explanatory","Learning"],"commands":[{"argumentHint":"","description":"Deep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report. (dynamic workflow)","name":"deep-research"},{"argumentHint":"[<project hint, e.g. \"Acme DS\">]","description":"Push a React design system to claude.ai/design. This runs a converter that bundles the real component code (from Storybook or a bare package) and uploads it. Use when the user runs /design-sync or says \"sync my design system to Claude Design\".","name":"design-sync"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Use this skill to configure the Claude Code harness via settings.json. Automated behaviors (\"from now on when X\", \"each time X\", \"whenever X\", \"before/after X\") require hooks configured in settings.json - the harness executes these, not Claude, so memory/preferences cannot fulfill them. Also use for: permissions (\"allow X\", \"add permission\", \"move permission to\"), env vars (\"set X=Y\"), hook troubleshooting, or any changes to settings.json/settings.local.json files. Examples: \"allow npm commands\", \"add bq permission to global settings\", \"move permission to user settings\", \"set DEBUG=true\", \"when claude stops show X\". For simple settings like theme/model, suggest the /config command.","name":"update-config"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Verify that a code change actually does what it's supposed to by running the app and observing behavior. Use when asked to verify a PR, confirm a fix works, test a change manually, check that a feature works, or validate local changes before pushing.","name":"verify"},{"argumentHint":"[issue description]","description":"Enable debug logging for this session and help diagnose issues","name":"debug"},{"argumentHint":"[low|medium|high|xhigh|max|ultra] [--fix] [--comment] [<target>]","description":"Review the current diff for correctness bugs and reuse/simplification/efficiency cleanups at the given effort level (low/medium: fewer, high-confidence findings; high→max: broader coverage, may include uncertain findings; ultra: deep multi-agent review in the cloud). Pass --comment to post findings as inline PR comments, or --fix to apply the findings to the working tree after the review.","name":"code-review"},{"argumentHint":"[<target>]","description":"Review the changed code for reuse, simplification, efficiency, and altitude cleanups, then apply the fixes. Quality only — it does not hunt for bugs; use /code-review for that.","name":"simplify"},{"argumentHint":"<instruction>","description":"Research and plan a large-scale change, then execute it in parallel across 5–30 isolated worktree agents that each open a PR.","name":"batch"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Scan your transcripts for common read-only Bash and MCP tool calls, then add a prioritized allowlist to project .claude/settings.json to reduce permission prompts.","name":"fewer-permission-prompts"},{"argumentHint":"[interval] [prompt]","description":"Run a prompt or slash command on a recurring interval (e.g. /loop 5m /foo). Omit the interval to let the model self-pace.","name":"loop"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Create, update, list, or run scheduled cloud agents (routines) that execute on a cron schedule.","name":"schedule"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Reference for the Claude API / Anthropic SDK — model ids, pricing, params, streaming, tool use, MCP, agents, caching, token counting, model migration.\nTRIGGER — read BEFORE opening the target file; don't skip because it \"looks like a one-liner\" — whenever: the prompt names Claude/Anthropic in any form (Claude, Anthropic, Fable, Opus, Sonnet, Haiku, `anthropic`, `@anthropic-ai`, `claude-*`, `us.anthropic.*`, `[1m]`); the user asks about an LLM (pricing/model choice/limits/caching) — never answer from memory; OR the task is LLM-shaped with provider unstated (agent/MCP/tool-definition/multi-agent/RAG/LLM-judge/computer-use; generate/summarize/extract/classify/rewrite/converse over NL; debugging refusals/cutoffs/streaming/tool-calls/tokens).\nSKIP only when another provider is being worked on (overrides all triggers): OpenAI/GPT/Gemini/Llama/Mistral/Cohere/Ollama named in the query; OR `grep -rE 'openai|langchain_openai|google.generativeai|genai|mistralai|cohere|ollama'` over the project hits (run this grep FIRST if no provider named — don't Read the file).","name":"claude-api"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Launch and drive this project's app to see a change working. Use when asked to run, start, or screenshot the app, or to confirm a change works in the real app (not just tests). First looks for a project skill that already covers launching the app; otherwise falls back to built-in patterns per project type (CLI, server, TUI, Electron, browser-driven, library).","name":"run"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Author or improve the run-<unit> skill — a per-project skill that tells agents how to build, launch, and drive this project's app. Use when the user asks to set up the project, get it running, write run instructions, or verify build/run steps work from a clean environment.","name":"run-skill-generator"},{"argumentHint":"[name]","description":"Start a new session with empty context; previous session stays on disk (resumable with /resume)","name":"clear"},{"argumentHint":"<optional custom summarization instructions>","description":"Free up context by summarizing the conversation so far","name":"compact"},{"argumentHint":"key=value","description":"Set a setting by key","name":"config"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Show current context usage","name":"context"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Dump the JS heap to ~/Desktop","name":"heapdump"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Initialize a new CLAUDE.md file with codebase documentation","name":"init"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Pick up skills added or changed on disk during this session","name":"reload-skills"},{"argumentHint":"[pr number]","description":"Review a GitHub pull request; for your working diff use /code-review","name":"review"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Complete a security review of the pending changes on the current branch","name":"security-review"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Configure usage credits to keep working when you hit a limit","name":"usage-credits"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Renamed to /usage-credits","name":"extra-usage"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Show session cost, plan usage, and what's contributing to your limits","name":"usage"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Generate a report analyzing your Claude Code sessions","name":"insights"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Set a goal — keep working until the condition is met","name":"goal"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Help teammates ramp on Claude Code with a guide from your usage","name":"team-onboarding"},{"description":"Analyze recent work, stage relevant files, and create a git commit with a clear, informative commit message.","name":"tugplug:commit"},{"argumentHint":"[plan-path] [; Step N | Steps N-M]","description":"Vet a plan (or a step range within it) BEFORE implementation — assess plan quality, coherence, technical choices, and strategy; check it against the tuglaws and the real code; then rule \"fixups needed\" or \"clear to implement\"","name":"tugplug:vet"},{"argumentHint":"[idea] [→ output-path]","description":"Devise an implementation plan in-thread — clarify the idea, write it against the devise skeleton, validate it — ready for /tugplug:implement","name":"tugplug:devise"},{"argumentHint":"[plan-path] [; Step N | Steps N-M]","description":"Audit the implementation work for a plan (or a step range) AFTER it's built — assess code quality, coherence, technical choices, and architecture; audit it against the tuglaws and the real diff; then rule \"fixups needed\" or \"codebase is in good shape\"","name":"tugplug:audit"},{"argumentHint":"[plan-path] [Step N | Steps N-M]","description":"Implement a plan into a tested build on an isolated worktree — walk a single step, a step range, or the whole plan; agentless, in-thread, committing per step, stopping for review before merge","name":"tugplug:implement"},{"argumentHint":"[name] [instruction|status|join|release]","description":"Quick, plan-less, worktree-isolated work — agentless, in-thread, committing per round, stopping for review before merge","name":"tugplug:dash"}],"effort":null,"ipc_version":2,"models":[{"description":"Opus 4.8 with 1M context · Best for everyday, complex tasks","displayName":"Default (recommended)","supportedEffortLevels":["low","medium","high","xhigh","max"],"supportsEffort":true,"value":"default"},{"description":"Opus 4.8 with 1M context · Best for everyday, complex tasks","displayName":"Opus","supportedEffortLevels":["low","medium","high","xhigh","max"],"supportsEffort":true,"value":"opus[1m]"},{"description":"Sonnet 5 · Efficient for routine tasks","displayName":"Sonnet","supportedEffortLevels":["low","medium","high","xhigh","max"],"supportsEffort":true,"value":"sonnet"},{"description":"Haiku 4.5 · Fastest for quick answers","displayName":"Haiku","value":"haiku"}],"output_style":"default","tug_session_id":"{{uuid}}","type":"session_capabilities","version":"2.1.197"}
